@EndNode

@Node "Introduction" "Short description"

When do you have to make a filerequest from your favourite BBS, you have
three choices:
- execute Spot (or a similar program) only to select the filerequest option
- you edit your .REQ via a text editor (not very amusing;)

or

- you utilise fREQ !!

fREQ is a very simple program to create a frequest file via a very simple GUI.

Feature overview:

 -  MUI 3.0 or better required
 -  online help
 -  support for BBS filelists
 -  an internal BBS database
 -  no know bugs ;-))


@{"Installation" link "Installation"}.
@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "Installation"

To install the fREQ program simply copy the file "fREQ" to your hard disk and
the "fREQ.config" file to the S: directory or where you want on your hard disk.
Remember to set the corresponding PREFSFILE tooltype in the fREQ2 icon file.

"fREQ.config" is not necessary, but it's a good example to show how to enter
the data for a BBS.


@{"Usage" link "Usage"}.
@EndNode

@Node "Usage" "Usage"

fREQ is a very simple program to master.

* To insert a filename to frequest:

        select the "Filename" gadget and enter the filename

        or

        press the spacebar or the "ADD" button and enter the filename


* To delete a filename from the list:

        select the file to delete with the mouse, clear the name from the
        "Filename" gadget (AMIGA-X) and press RETURN


* To enter the FIDO number of your BOSS:

        enter the fidonumber in the "BOSS" gadget (ex: 2:301/231)

        or

        press the "BOSS" button ("B"): a new window with the list of available
        addresses will be opened. Select the adress of your choice


* To add a BOSS adress to the BOSS list:

        type the BOSS fido address into the "BOSS" gadget.
        Press the "BOSS" button (or the right mouse button)
        Select the SAVE option from the addresses window.


* When you select a BOSS number, fREQ will scan the outbound: directory sear-
  ching for an existing frequest file.
  If a file is found, the list of request programs will be shown in the 
  "Files to request" list.
  If you select the "VERIFY INBOUND" gadget, fREQ will scan the Inbound: 
  directory verifying if the files present in the "Files to request" list have
  already been downloaded.
  It's a very usefull option when your modem loses the line during a filerequest.


@EndNode

@Node "History" "History of fREQ"

1.5:
- first public release

2.0:
- Now fREQ is a MUI application

2.1:
- Fixed a bug with the preference file;
- Now there is no more a limit to the number of files
  that you frequest.

2.2:
- Added external filelist support:
  now you can select the files that you want download directly
  from the BBS filelist.
- Added, in the preferences window, a list of know suffix to
  utilise with the external filelist support.

2.3:
- Added support for the bubble help feature of MUI 3.0
  now you can have online help.
- Several (2) small bugfixes:
  now the fREQ application is really bugless ;-)

2.4:
- Internal version

2.5:
- Added the UPPER CASE option
- I've changed my email address

@EndNode

